description: {"blocks":[{"key":"58qfh","text":"This protocol is the basic LC and MS running parameters for lipids or very hydrophobic molecules. Most are singly charged. steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"6818v","text":"Add 10 uL of Splash Mix standard to the extracted lipids. Dry samples under liquid nitrogen at 40C. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dgsmi","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b4gb2","text":"Mix well using a “figure-eight” movement of the vials in the bench. Transfer the sample to a new vial with borosilicate inserts. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":25,"length":5},{"style":"italic","offset":67,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ersh3","text":"Make sure there is no air in the bottom of the inserts  add the vials into the autosampler of the UPLC Vanquish system.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7kail","text":"In the sequence setup view of the Xcalibur software include each sample in a row filling with: file name, sample ID, folder directory to save results, directory for the acquisition method, vial position and injection volume. Normally use 10% of each sample for injection.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
